# Accessibility Statement

**Coeliacs Like Beer Too**  
*Last updated: 10/07/2025*

## Our Commitment

We are committed to making coeliacslikebeer.co.uk accessible to everyone, including people with disabilities. We believe that finding gluten-free beer should be easy for all members of the coeliac community.

## Accessibility Standards

This website aims to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. These guidelines help make web content more accessible for people with disabilities.

## What We've Done

### Navigation and Structure
- ✅ Clear, logical page structure with proper headings
- ✅ Consistent navigation throughout the site
- ✅ Skip links to main content areas
- ✅ Descriptive page titles and link text

### Visual Design
- ✅ High contrast color scheme for better readability
- ✅ Text remains readable when zoomed to 200%
- ✅ No content relies solely on color to convey information
- ✅ Focus indicators for keyboard navigation

### Interactive Elements
- ✅ All functionality available via keyboard
- ✅ Touch targets are at least 44px for mobile users
- ✅ Form fields have clear labels and error messages
- ✅ Buttons and links have descriptive text

### Images and Media
- ✅ Alternative text for all meaningful images
- ✅ Icons supplemented with text labels
- ✅ Maps include text-based alternatives

### Technical Features
- ✅ Semantic HTML markup
- ✅ ARIA labels where appropriate
- ✅ Responsive design for all devices
- ✅ Works without JavaScript for core functionality

## Known Limitations

We're continuously working to improve accessibility. Current limitations include:

- **Interactive Map**: Some map features may be challenging for screen reader users (text-based search alternatives provided)
- **User-Generated Images**: Photos uploaded by community members may lack alt text
- **Third-Party Content**: Some embedded content (maps, analytics) may have accessibility limitations

## Assistive Technologies

This website has been tested with:
- Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
- Keyboard-only navigation
- Voice control software
- Zoom software up to 200%

## Feedback and Contact

We welcome feedback on the accessibility of this website. If you encounter any barriers or have suggestions for improvement:

**Contact Methods:**
- Email: legal@coeliacslikebeer.co.uk (Subject: "Accessibility Feedback")
- Describe the specific page and issue you encountered
- Include details about your assistive technology if relevant

**Response Time:**
We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 3 business days and implement fixes within 2 weeks where possible.

## Ongoing Improvements

We regularly:
- Review and test our website's accessibility
- Provide accessibility training for our team
- Consult with disability community members
- Update content to meet evolving standards

## Legal Compliance

This statement reflects our commitment to accessibility and our efforts to comply with:
- UK Equality Act 2010
- EU Web Accessibility Directive
- Section 508 (US Federal accessibility requirements)

## Alternative Access

If you cannot access content or features on our website, we can provide information in alternative formats:
- Large print versions of key information
- Email summaries of pub listings for specific areas
- Phone assistance for finding gluten-free options

Contact us to request alternative formats.

## Third-Party Content

Some content is provided by third parties (maps, analytics). We work with providers who share our commitment to accessibility, but cannot guarantee the accessibility of all third-party features.

## Updates

We review this accessibility statement annually and update it when we make significant changes to the website.

---

*This statement was prepared in accordance with the UK's accessibility regulations and reflects our ongoing commitment to digital inclusion.*
